[{"text": "This cell phone", "start": 15.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "started its trajectory", "start": 18.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in an artisanal mine", "start": 21.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the Eastern Congo.", "start": 23.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's mined by armed gangs", "start": 25.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "using slaves, child slaves,", "start": 27.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "what the U.N. Security Council", "start": 29.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "calls \"blood minerals,\"", "start": 31.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "then traveled into some components", "start": 33.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and ended up in a factory", "start": 35.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in Shinjin in China.", "start": 37.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That factory -- over a dozen people have committed suicide", "start": 39.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "already this year.", "start": 42.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "One man died after working a 36-hour shift.", "start": 44.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We all love chocolate.", "start": 48.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We buy it for our kids.", "start": 50.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Eighty percent of the cocoa comes from Cote d'Ivoire and Ghana", "start": 52.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and it's harvested by children.", "start": 55.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Cote d'Ivoire, we have a huge problem of child slaves.", "start": 58.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Children have been trafficked from other conflict zones", "start": 60.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to come and work on the coffee plantations.", "start": 63.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Heparin -- a blood thinner,", "start": 66.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a pharmaceutical product --", "start": 68.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "starts out in artisanal workshops", "start": 70.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "like this in China,", "start": 73.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because the active ingredient", "start": 75.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "comes from pigs' intestines.", "start": 77.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Your diamond -- you've all heard, probably seen the movie \"Blood Diamond.\"", "start": 80.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is a mine in Zimbabwe", "start": 83.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "right now.", "start": 85.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Cotton: Uzbekistan is the second biggest", "start": 87.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "exporter of cotton on Earth.", "start": 89.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Every year when it comes to the cotton harvest,", "start": 91.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the government shuts down the schools,", "start": 94.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "puts the kids in buses, buses them to the cotton fields", "start": 96.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to spend three weeks harvesting the cotton.", "start": 99.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's forced child labor", "start": 102.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "on an institutional scale.", "start": 104.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And all of those products probably end their lives", "start": 107.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in a dump like this one in Manila.", "start": 110.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "These places, these origins,", "start": 112.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "represent governance gaps.", "start": 115.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That's the politest description", "start": 117.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I have for them.", "start": 119.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "These are the dark pools", "start": 122.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "where global supply chains begin --", "start": 124.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the global supply chains,", "start": 127.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which bring us our favorite brand name products.", "start": 129.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Some of these governance gaps", "start": 132.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "are run by rogue states.", "start": 135.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Some of them are not states anymore at all.", "start": 138.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They're failed states.", "start": 140.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Some of them", "start": 142.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are just countries who believe that deregulation or no regulation", "start": 144.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is the best way to attract investment,", "start": 147.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "promote trade.", "start": 150.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Either way, they present us", "start": 152.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with a huge moral and ethical dilemma.", "start": 154.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I know that none of us want to be accessories", "start": 158.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "after the fact", "start": 160.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of a human rights abuse", "start": 163.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in a global supply chain.", "start": 165.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But right now,", "start": 167.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "most of the companies involved in these supply chains", "start": 169.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "don't have any way", "start": 172.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of assuring us", "start": 174.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that nobody had to mortgage their future,", "start": 176.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "nobody had to sacrifice their rights", "start": 178.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to bring us our favorite", "start": 181.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "brand name product.", "start": 183.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Now, I didn't come here to depress you", "start": 186.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about the state of the global supply chain.", "start": 188.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We need a reality check.", "start": 191.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We need to recognize just how serious", "start": 193.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "a deficit of rights we have.", "start": 196.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is an independent republic,", "start": 199.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "probably a failed state.", "start": 201.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's definitely not a democratic state.", "start": 203.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And right now,", "start": 207.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that independent republic of the supply chain", "start": 209.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is not being governed", "start": 211.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in a way that would satisfy us,", "start": 213.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that we can engage in ethical trade or ethical consumption.", "start": 216.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now, that's not a new story.", "start": 220.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "You've seen the documentaries", "start": 222.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of sweatshops making garments", "start": 224.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "all over the world, even in developed countries.", "start": 226.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "You want to see the classic sweatshop,", "start": 229.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "meet me at Madison Square Garden,", "start": 231.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I'll take you down the street, and I'll show you a Chinese sweatshop.", "start": 233.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But take the example of heparin.", "start": 236.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's a pharmaceutical product.", "start": 239.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "You expect that the supply chain that gets it to the hospital,", "start": 241.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "probably squeaky clean.", "start": 244.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The problem is that the active ingredient in there --", "start": 248.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as I mentioned earlier --", "start": 250.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "comes from pigs.", "start": 252.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The main American manufacturer", "start": 254.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of that active ingredient", "start": 257.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "decided a few years ago to relocate to China", "start": 259.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "because it's the world's biggest supplier of pigs.", "start": 262.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And their factory in China --", "start": 265.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which probably is pretty clean --", "start": 267.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is getting all of the ingredients", "start": 270.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "from backyard abattoirs,", "start": 272.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "where families slaughter pigs", "start": 274.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and extract the ingredient.", "start": 276.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So a couple of years ago, we had a scandal", "start": 279.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which killed about 80 people around the world,", "start": 281.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "because of contaminants", "start": 283.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that crept into the heparin supply chain.", "start": 285.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Worse, some of the suppliers", "start": 288.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "realized that they could substitute a product", "start": 290.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "which mimicked heparin in tests.", "start": 294.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This substitute cost nine dollars a pound,", "start": 298.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "whereas real heparin, the real ingredient,", "start": 301.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "cost 900 dollars a pound.", "start": 304.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "A no-brainer.", "start": 307.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The problem was that it killed more people.", "start": 309.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And so you're asking yourself,", "start": 312.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"How come the U.S. Food and Drug Administration", "start": 314.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "allowed this to happen?", "start": 316.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "How did the Chinese State Agency for Food and Drugs", "start": 318.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "allow this to happen?\"", "start": 320.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And the answer is quite simple:", "start": 322.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the Chinese define these facilities", "start": 325.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "as chemical facilities, not pharmaceutical facilities,", "start": 327.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "so they don't audit them.", "start": 330.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And the USFDA", "start": 332.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "has a jurisdictional problem.", "start": 334.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This is offshore.", "start": 336.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They actually do conduct a few investigations overseas --", "start": 338.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about a dozen a year -- maybe 20 in a good year.", "start": 340.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "There are 500", "start": 343.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of these facilities", "start": 345.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "producing active ingredients in China alone.", "start": 347.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In fact, about 80 percent", "start": 350.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "of the active ingredients in medicines now", "start": 353.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "come from offshore,", "start": 355.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "particularly China and India,", "start": 357.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and we don't have a governance system.", "start": 359.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We don't have a regulatory system", "start": 362.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "able to ensure", "start": 364.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that that production is safe.", "start": 366.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We don't have a system to ensure", "start": 370.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that human rights, basic dignity,", "start": 372.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are ensured.", "start": 374.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So at a national level --", "start": 377.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and we work in about 60 different countries --", "start": 380.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "at a national level", "start": 382.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we've got a serious breakdown in the ability of governments", "start": 384.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to regulate production", "start": 386.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "on their own soil.", "start": 389.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the real problem with the global supply chain", "start": 392.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is that it's supranational.", "start": 394.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So governments who are failing,", "start": 396.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who are dropping the ball", "start": 398.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "at a national level,", "start": 400.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "have even less ability to get their arms around the problem", "start": 402.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "at an international level.", "start": 404.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And you can just look at the headlines.", "start": 407.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Take Copenhagen last year --", "start": 409.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "complete failure of governments", "start": 412.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to do the right thing", "start": 414.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in the face of an international challenge.", "start": 416.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Take the G20 meeting a couple of weeks ago --", "start": 419.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "stepped back from its commitments of just a few months ago.", "start": 422.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "You can take any one", "start": 427.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the major global challenges we've discussed this week", "start": 429.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and ask yourself, where is the leadership from governments", "start": 432.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to step up and come up with solutions,", "start": 435.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "responses,", "start": 438.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to those international problems?", "start": 440.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And the simple answer is they can't. They're national.", "start": 443.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Their voters are local.", "start": 447.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They have parochial interests.", "start": 449.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They can't subordinate those interests", "start": 451.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the greater global public good.", "start": 453.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So, if we're going to ensure the delivery", "start": 456.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the key public goods", "start": 458.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "at an international level --", "start": 460.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in this case, in the global supply chain --", "start": 462.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we have to come up with a different mechanism.", "start": 465.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We need a different machine.", "start": 468.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Fortunately, we have some examples.", "start": 472.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "In the 1990s,", "start": 476.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there were a whole series of scandals", "start": 478.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "concerning the production of brand name goods in the U.S. --", "start": 480.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "child labor, forced labor,", "start": 482.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "serious health and safety abuses.", "start": 484.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And eventually President Clinton, in 1996,", "start": 487.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "convened a meeting at the White House,", "start": 489.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "invited industry, human rights NGOs,", "start": 492.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "trade unions, the Department of Labor,", "start": 495.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "got them all in a room", "start": 497.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and said, \"Look,", "start": 499.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I don't want globalization to be a race to the bottom.", "start": 501.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I don't know how to prevent that,", "start": 503.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but I'm at least going to use my good offices", "start": 505.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to get you folks together", "start": 507.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to come up with a response.\"", "start": 509.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So they formed a White House task force,", "start": 512.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and they spent about three years arguing", "start": 514.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "about who takes how much responsibility", "start": 517.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the global supply chain.", "start": 520.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Companies didn't feel it was their responsibility.", "start": 523.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They don't own those facilities.", "start": 526.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They don't employ those workers.", "start": 528.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They're not legally liable.", "start": 530.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Everybody else at the table", "start": 533.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "said, \"Folks, that doesn't cut it.", "start": 535.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "You have a custodial duty, a duty of care,", "start": 537.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to make sure that that product", "start": 540.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "gets from wherever to the store", "start": 542.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in a way that allows us to consume it,", "start": 545.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "without fear of our safety,", "start": 548.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or without having to sacrifice our conscience", "start": 551.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "to consume that product.\"", "start": 555.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So they agreed, \"Okay, what we'll do", "start": 557.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is we agree on a common set of standards,", "start": 560.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "code of conduct.", "start": 562.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We'll apply that throughout", "start": 564.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "our global supply chain", "start": 566.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "regardless of ownership or control.", "start": 568.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We'll make it part of the contract.\"", "start": 570.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And that was a stroke of absolute genius,", "start": 573.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "because what they did", "start": 576.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was they harnessed the power of the contract,", "start": 578.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "private power,", "start": 581.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to deliver public goods.", "start": 583.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And let's face it,", "start": 585.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the contract from a major multinational brand", "start": 587.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to a supplier in India or China", "start": 589.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "has much more persuasive value", "start": 592.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "than the local labor law,", "start": 594.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the local environmental regulations,", "start": 596.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the local human rights standards.", "start": 598.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Those factories will probably never see an inspector.", "start": 601.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "If the inspector did come along,", "start": 604.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it would be amazing if they were able", "start": 607.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to resist the bribe.", "start": 609.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Even if they did their jobs,", "start": 613.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and they cited those facilities for their violations,", "start": 615.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the fine would be derisory.", "start": 619.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But you lose that contract", "start": 621.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for a major brand name,", "start": 623.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that's the difference", "start": 625.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "between staying in business or going bankrupt.", "start": 627.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That makes a difference.", "start": 630.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So what we've been able to do", "start": 632.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is we've been able to harness", "start": 634.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the power and the influence", "start": 636.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the only truly transnational institution", "start": 638.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the global supply chain,", "start": 641.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that of the multinational company,", "start": 643.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and get them to do the right thing,", "start": 646.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "get them to use that power for good,", "start": 648.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to deliver the key public goods.", "start": 651.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now of course, this doesn't come naturally", "start": 655.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to multinational companies.", "start": 657.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They weren't set up to do this. They're set up to make money.", "start": 659.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But they are extremely efficient organizations.", "start": 662.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They have resources,", "start": 665.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and if we can add the will, the commitment,", "start": 667.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "they know how to deliver that product.", "start": 670.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now, getting there is not easy.", "start": 675.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Those supply chains I put up on the screen earlier,", "start": 678.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "they're not there.", "start": 681.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "You need a safe space.", "start": 683.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "You need a place where people can come together,", "start": 685.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "sit down without fear of judgment,", "start": 688.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "without recrimination,", "start": 690.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to actually face the problem,", "start": 692.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "agree on the problem and come up with solutions.", "start": 694.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We can do it. The technical solutions are there.", "start": 697.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The problem is the lack of trust, the lack of confidence,", "start": 700.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "the lack of partnership", "start": 703.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "between NGOs, campaign groups,", "start": 705.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "civil society organizations", "start": 707.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and multinational companies.", "start": 710.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "If we can put those two together in a safe space,", "start": 713.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "get them to work together,", "start": 716.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we can deliver public goods right now,", "start": 718.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "or in extremely short supply.", "start": 721.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is a radical proposition,", "start": 724.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and it's crazy to think", "start": 726.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that if you're a 15-year-old Bangladeshi girl", "start": 728.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "leaving your rural village", "start": 731.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to go and work in a factory in Dhaka --", "start": 734.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "22, 23, 24 dollars a month --", "start": 737.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "your best chance of enjoying rights at work", "start": 742.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "is if that factory is producing", "start": 745.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for a brand name company", "start": 747.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "which has got a code of conduct", "start": 749.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and made that code of conduct part of the contract.", "start": 751.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It's crazy.", "start": 755.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Multinationals are protecting human rights.", "start": 757.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "I know there's going to be disbelief.", "start": 759.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "You'll say, \"How can we trust them?\"", "start": 761.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Well, we don't.", "start": 763.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It's the old arms control phrase:", "start": 765.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"Trust, but verify.\"", "start": 767.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So we audit.", "start": 769.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We take their supply chain, we take all the factory names,", "start": 771.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we do a random sample,", "start": 774.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we send inspectors on an unannounced basis", "start": 776.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to inspect those facilities,", "start": 779.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and then we publish the results.", "start": 781.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Transparency is absolutely critical to this.", "start": 783.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "You can call yourself responsible,", "start": 787.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "but responsibility without accountability", "start": 790.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "often doesn't work.", "start": 793.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So what we're doing is, we're not only enlisting the multinationals,", "start": 795.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "we're giving them the tools to deliver this public good --", "start": 798.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "respect for human rights --", "start": 801.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and we're checking.", "start": 803.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "You don't need to believe me. You shouldn't believe me.", "start": 805.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Go to the website. Look at the audit results.", "start": 807.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Ask yourself, is this company behaving", "start": 810.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in a socially responsible way?", "start": 812.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Can I buy that product", "start": 815.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "without compromising my ethics?", "start": 817.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That's the way the system works.", "start": 820.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I hate the idea", "start": 825.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that governments are not protecting human rights around the world.", "start": 827.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I hate the idea", "start": 830.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that governments have dropped this ball", "start": 832.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and I can't get used to the idea", "start": 834.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that somehow we can't get them to do their jobs.", "start": 837.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I've been at this for 30 years,", "start": 840.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and in that time I've seen", "start": 842.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the ability, the commitment, the will of government", "start": 844.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to do this decline,", "start": 847.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and I don't see them making a comeback right now.", "start": 849.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "So we started out thinking", "start": 852.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "this was a stopgap measure.", "start": 854.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We're now thinking that, in fact,", "start": 856.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "this is probably the start", "start": 859.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of a new way of regulating and addressing", "start": 861.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "international challenges.", "start": 864.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Call it network governance. Call it what you will.", "start": 866.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The private actors,", "start": 869.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "companies and NGOs,", "start": 872.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "are going to have to get together", "start": 874.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to face the major challenges we are going to face.", "start": 876.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Just look at pandemics --", "start": 878.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "swine flu, bird flu, H1N1.", "start": 880.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Look at the health systems in so many countries.", "start": 883.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Do they have the resources", "start": 885.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to face up to a serious pandemic?", "start": 887.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "No.", "start": 890.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Could the private sector and NGOs", "start": 892.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "get together and marshal a response?", "start": 895.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Absolutely.", "start": 897.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "What they lack is that safe space", "start": 899.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to come together, agree", "start": 901.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and move to action.", "start": 903.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That's what we're trying to provide.", "start": 905.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I know as well", "start": 909.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that this often seems", "start": 911.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "like an overwhelming level of responsibility", "start": 913.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for people to assume.", "start": 915.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "\"You want me to deliver human rights", "start": 917.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "throughout my global supply chain.", "start": 919.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "There are thousands of suppliers in there.\"", "start": 921.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It seems too daunting, too dangerous,", "start": 924.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "for any company to take on.", "start": 927.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "But there are companies.", "start": 929.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We have 4,000 companies who are members.", "start": 931.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Some of them are very, very large companies.", "start": 934.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The sporting goods industry, in particular,", "start": 936.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "stepped up to the plate and have done it.", "start": 938.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The example, the role model, is there.", "start": 941.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And whenever we discuss", "start": 945.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "one of these problems that we have to address --", "start": 947.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "child labor in cottonseed farms in India --", "start": 949.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "this year we will monitor 50,000 cottonseed farms in India.", "start": 952.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It seems overwhelming.", "start": 956.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The numbers just make you want to zone out.", "start": 958.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "But we break it down to some basic realities.", "start": 961.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And human rights", "start": 964.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "comes down to a very simple proposition:", "start": 966.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "can I give this person their dignity back?", "start": 969.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Poor people,", "start": 972.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "people whose human rights have been violated --", "start": 974.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the crux of that", "start": 976.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is the loss of dignity,", "start": 978.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the lack of dignity.", "start": 980.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "It starts with just giving people back their dignity.", "start": 982.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "I was sitting in a slum outside Gurgaon", "start": 985.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "just next to Delhi,", "start": 988.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "one of the flashiest, brightest new cities", "start": 990.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "popping up in India right now,", "start": 993.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and I was talking to workers", "start": 996.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who worked in garment sweatshops down the road,", "start": 998.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and I asked them what message they would like me to take to the brands.", "start": 1000.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They didn't say money.", "start": 1004.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "They said, \"The people who employ us", "start": 1007.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "treat us like we are less than human,", "start": 1010.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "like we don't exist.", "start": 1013.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Please ask them to treat us like human beings.\"", "start": 1015.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "That's my simple understanding of human rights.", "start": 1019.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That's my simple proposition to you,", "start": 1021.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "my simple plea to every decision-maker", "start": 1024.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in this room, everybody out there.", "start": 1027.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We can all make a decision", "start": 1029.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to come together", "start": 1031.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and pick up the balls and run with the balls", "start": 1033.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that governments have dropped.", "start": 1036.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "If we don't do it,", "start": 1038.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we're abandoning hope,", "start": 1040.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we're abandoning our essential humanity,", "start": 1042.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and I know that's not a place we want to be,", "start": 1045.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and we don't have to be there.", "start": 1047.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "So I appeal to you.", "start": 1049.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Join us, come into that safe space,", "start": 1051.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and let's start to make this happen.", "start": 1053.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Thank you very much.", "start": 1055.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 1057.26, "duration": 3.0}]